x=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just a few raid questions..</span><hr size=1> Hole Raids so to speak tend to be guild events, as it is more of a mid ranged zone.  I am sure some guilds do &quot;raid&quot; there, try the LFM section of this board.  That being said, I would guess that the raids there are rather rare.  Those paladins I know who have killed the mob have brought their own crew for the most part.<br><br>Naggy/Vox are FCFS atm, so if they are up, the best chance you have is to lead a raid yourself.  One word of caution though, do not claim too much loot, or you will find it hard to recruit people to come to your raid.  Best ofluck to you.<br><br>Eoral<br>Evoluxa <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujuujuu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Juujuu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>*Poke Tigana!*</span><br>  Posts: 1533<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/8/02 1:09:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm71.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just a few raid questions..</span><hr size=1> While the epic is good weapon, it's insanely difficult to acquire both books.  People can spend an entire year trying to acquire their epic.  My advice would be to save up your cash and try to buy something comparable in stats.  The first thing that comes to mind is a black acrylia halbard.  It's got a 40/44 ratio I think, 2h slash, with a small lifetap proc, and they sell for about 12-15k from tradeskill smiths.  Whenever the Dain is killed, he often drops a 2h slasher that no one wants.  I think that paladins can use it, though not all races can.  I think it's limited to short races, though I'm not sure.  In any case, I can't think of one that hasn't rotted or been twinked in months.  I've also seen multiple 2h slasher rot in akheva semi-deep in.  The cloaked mobs drop them on occasion, and they have stats similar to 39/44 with some stats.  As neat as it is getting your epic, there's something to be said for getting a comparable item in 1/10 the time. <p>=============================<br>Juujuu Bigmojo<br>60 Shaman of one race or another</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urinvar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rinvar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/21/02 1:19:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm71.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Just a few raid questions..</span><hr size=1> I totally agree with Juujuu, Paladin epic is nice, but definately not worth hanging around 52 for ages, particulary not with all the alternatives out there these days.  If you want to do some of your epic, do the soulfire and ghoulbane first (Soulfire looks pretty neat and the charges of Cheal are precious). <p><html><body><BR><IMG  src="http://www.getwasted.net/graphics/rinsig.jpg" width=300></BR></body></html></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm71.showPrevMessage?topicID=121.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm71.showNextMessage?topicID=121.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm71.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=3><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~eqmaximus/brell/addreply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valig